 doctor and the manager appeared. “Voilà,” said the doctor in a deeply hurt voice addressing the manager and pointing at me. “There—that gentleman not only took offense at something I never said, but has now insulted me, refusing to hear me out and being extremely rude. Will you please talk to him. I am not used to such manners.”

“Il faut s’expliquer—you must thrash it out,” said the manager glowering at me darkly. “I’m sure that monsieur himself—”

